The paper deals with a graph theory problem related to resource allocation, encoding theory, and network routing, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The problem is also related to planar graphs and chordless paths, which are topics in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents an algorithmic result, which could place it in the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category.
